<title>SPAIN: IFC ups equity-linked matador to 47.5 bln pta.</title>
<headline>IFC ups equity-linked matador to 47.5 bln pta.</headline>
<dateline>MADRID 1997-02-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>The International Finance Corporation (IFC) has increased by a further 9.5 billion pesetas a six-tranche matador bond, for a total of 47.5 billion pesetas from an initial 38 billion.</p>
<p>Lead manager Deutsche Morgan Grenfell said on Friday the issue price is at par, and payment date is February 17.</p>
<p>All other terms remain the same as the initial issue on December 23.</p>
<p>All tranches have a variable coupon linked to a basket of FTSE, DAX, CAC and IBEX indices. All bonds mature in August 2002. There are varying redemption amounts for each tranche.</p>
<p>-- Madrid Newsroom, + 341 585 8340</p>
